Libraries Required:
---vtk

---if not installed then install by opening the command prompt and type pip install vtk and hit enter

######################################################################################################################################

Instructions to execute the python script -

1. Open the folder where the Python script is located.
2. Click on the address bar at the top of the window and type "cmd" and hit enter. This will open the command prompt window.
In the command prompt, type "python" followed by the name of your Python script file (including the ".py" extension) and hit enter. 
This will execute the Python script.

For --- Question 1:

In the command prompt, type "python" followed by the name of your Python script file (assignment2_question1.py) and hit enter.[python assignment2_question1.py]
This will execute the Python script for question1.
Type the value of isovalue(c) and press enter.
The program will generate the isocontour as a VTKPolyData object and write it out to the same folder as a VTKPolyDatafile (isocontour.vtp file)

For --- Question 2:

In the command prompt, type "python" followed by the name of your Python script file (assignment2_question2.py) and hit enter.[python assignment2_question2.py]
This will execute the Python script for question2.
Input yes for phong shading else input no and press enter.

